foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: FAA - The number of pending requests at the beginning of FY 2012 is 82 lower than reported in last year's annual report as pending at the end of FY 2011. The adjustment primarily reflects requests where final action was taken by all apppropriate FAA offices in FY 2011, but not all database closures were entered into the database until FY 2012. (Note: FOIA requests assigned to multiple FAA offices are not closed until the last FAA office responds to the requester.)

FHWA, FMCSA, and MARAD - The number of pending at the beginning of FY 2012 is 4 lower (FHWA), 1 lower (FMCSA), and 5 lower (MARAD), than reported in last year's annual report as pending at the end of FY 2011. The adjustment primarily reflects requests where final action was taken in FY 2011, but the close-outs were not captured as closed in the database until FY 2012.

PHMSA - The number of pending requests at the beginning of FY 2012 is 1 higher than report in last year's annual report as pending at the end of FY 2011. This adjustment reflects an additional request that was received in FY 2011, but not logged in until FY 2012.
For the reasons stated above, the "agency overall" number of requests pending at the beginning of FY 2012 is 91 lower than reported in last year's annual report as pending at the end of FY 2011.
